# 2-Bit Ripple-Carry Adder (Logic Programming Style)
# This is a diagnostic test to confirm that our syntax is correct
# and that the 4-bit version is crashing due to complexity.

# Component: Full Adder definition
fa_s(a,b,cin):=(a+b)+cin
fa_cout(a,b,cin):=(a&b)|(cin&(a+b))

# 2-bit Adder
c[0]():=F # Initial Carry-in

# Input Stimulus: 2 + 1 = 3 (10 + 01 = 11)
# Input A = 2 (10)
a[0]():=F
a[1]():=T

# Input B = 1 (01)
b[0]():=T
b[1]():=F

# Stage 0
s[0]():=fa_s(a[0](),b[0](),c[0]())
c[1]():=fa_cout(a[0](),b[0](),c[0]())

# Stage 1
s[1]():=fa_s(a[1](),b[1](),c[1]())
c[2]():=fa_cout(a[1](),b[1](),c[1]())

# Verification Query: Check the sum bits for 3 (11)
# s[0] should be T, s[1] should be T, c[2] should be F
correct_result():=s[0]()&s[1]()&(c[2]())'
solve correct_result()
